All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
Admin
This class contains the methods that can be used for an admin in the library system.
AdminDeleteLibrarian
This class displays the form that requires the admin to enter the librarian's employee "id" key to search for the librarian in the librarians.json file and delete the record that matches the key.
AdminOptions
After a successful Admin login, this class creates the page which shows the admin a list of options that can be chosen.
AdminRegisterLibrarian
This class displays the form to gather the data to register a new librarian.
AdminViewLibrarians
This class creates a list of the currently registered librarians in the system.
Librarian
This class manages all the students that registered in the system.
LibrarianAddBook
This class is responsible for adding a new book in the library.
LibrarianDeleteBook
This class is responsible for deleting a book identified by the passed ISBN.
LibrarianOptions
This class is responsible for showing three options to the logged in librarian.
LibrarianViewBooks
This class is responsible for showing the current catalogue for the library.
Library
This class is responsible for creating the primary stage and a scene for that stage which will render multiple roots as the user progresses through the application.
LoginAndRegister
This class is responsible for creating the primary stage and a scene to login.
Main
This class defines a main method whose only task is to call the Library class's main method.
Student
This class manages all the students that registered in the system.
StudentLogin
This class is responsible for creating a login page for the student.
StudentOptions
This class is responsible for showing two options to the logged in student.
StudentRegister
This class is responsible for creating a register page for the student.
StudentViewBooksAndBorrowBook
This class is responsible for showing the current catalogue for the library.
StudentViewBorrowedBooksAndReturnBooks
This class is responsible for showing the currently borrowed books for logged in student.
